title: Arrest ends three-hour police chase
text:
Man arrested after three-hour police chase ends in Redcliffe Jack McKay, The Courier-Mail February 3, 2017 4:41pm 
A MAN has been taken into police custody after a mammoth three-hour police chase at Redcliffe. 
It is understood police attempted to intercept the man’s vehicle on Spring St about 11.40am, but the man allegedly refused to pull over. JUST IN: Heavy police presence at Kippa-Ring train station. Updates to follow. #9News pic.twitter.com/hyrSSX1FMg — Nine News Brisbane (@9NewsBrisbane) February 3, 2017 
Police tracked the vehicle for several more hours before he was cornered near Kippa Ring train station. 
He has been taken into police custody. 
It is believed under cover police cars were used in the operation. #BREAKING : One person in custody after reports a stolen vehicle was being driven erratically around Redcliffe. #qldtraffic #7News pic.twitter.com/FyZ3QjkgzR — 7 News Queensland (@7NewsQueensland) February 3, 2017 
Elsewhere in the southeast, rail commuters face a troublesome journey home as trains have been suspended in both directions on the Cleveland Line between Thornside and Lota stations due to a police incident. At the request of police, Cleveland line trains are suspended both directions https://t.co/huJkwOjq1G #TLAlert #TLClevelandline 
Translink says customers can expect delays of up to 30 minutes. Most viewed
